Lines.LineContent: ANNUAL REPORT of SALMON STREAMS and SPAWNING POPULATION
SPAWNING RUN TIMING and ESTIMATED NUMBER
(A) Enhancement activities or intense biological activities.
(C) Obstructions or changes in habitat with recommendations.
(D) Large variation în sex ratio or unusual number of jacks.
(E) High/low water flow level during spawning.
(A) Evidence of erosion and silting. Give extent or percent of stream bed affected:
Major silting in lower 300 m. of main branch.
(B) Particulars of scouring of spawning beds or change in course of stream :
Course change at 300 m. in center branch due to silting and gravel movement. Early in the spawning season, when the water levels were low, part of the main
(C) Water levels flow, normal, abnormal. If abnormal, details should be given :
Consistently good water levels through the spawning period. Slight flooding during the last two weeks of October.
(D) Particulars of distribution of salmon over stream bed :
Slight impact from birds and bears.
(F) Evidence of digging up eggs by late spawning fish :
This system should be carefully watched over the next few seasons, as obstructions will probably develop. The course change at this time seems to be only
a problem under low water conditions, an attempt to change this would probably be unsuccessful.
COMMENTS ON ANY OTHER CONDITIONS AFFECTING THIS STREAM
Good seed of chums this year, but the top ol the system was only lightly utilized.
Logging activity in the area has ceased.
